1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-103.9c of Title 70, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. Beginning in the 2025-2026 school year, each school district
5 shall conduct an annual fitness assessment, as approved by the State
6 Board of Education, each school year for students in grades three
7 through twelve, to be conducted in a course that satisfies the
8 physical education program required pursuant to Section 11-103.9 of
9 Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes or during the school year where
10 the assessment can be administered by trained personnel, including,
11 but not limited to, school nurses, physical education and health
12 teachers, coaches and any other certified school employees. The
13 assessments shall include methods deemed by the Board as appropriate
14 to ascertain levels of student physical fitness and factors and
15 standards required in subsection B of this section. A school
16 district shall not be required to conduct the annual fitness
17 assessment for students with a disability or other condition that
18 requires an exemption as determined by the State Department of
19 Education.
20 B. The State Department of Education shall adopt an assessment
21 instrument to be used by all school districts in assessing student
22 physical fitness that includes standards accessible to districts
23 which adequately express the most current and widely accepted best
24 practices and benchmarks in the areas of student health and physical
